  <notes>
    <note handle="_1032dde5d167617e6ddf13adc544" change="1781065723" id="N0013" type="Family Note">
      <text>We know little about this family as they were absent from the longhouse beforeJulia's recollection.</text>
    </note>
    <note handle="_1032ddea450054872917df0eb9f5" change="1781065752" id="N0014" type="Family Note">
      <text>We know little about this family as they were absent from the longhouse beforeJulia's recollection.</text>
    </note>
    <note handle="_1032de1c5d262d644ecca6f3879e" change="1781066081" id="N0015" type="Person Note">
      <text>Think she had 4 or 5 children. Married to brother of a famous kung fu artist, Way Fai Hoy, who ran a Lion Dance association.He died young</text>
    </note>
    <note handle="_1032de44e7097182668ce94aa9fd" change="1781066346" id="N0016" type="Person Note">
      <text>Her husband is the one who got seduced by a Fillipino lady and lost all his savings. Had to return to SIngapore.</text>
    </note>
    <note handle="_dc72ef25d0b1f5afd730122c2ac" change="1514913728" id="N0000" type="Source Note">
      <text>Telephone conversation on 2nd Jan 2018

Basically, Laina phoned back in response to 3 questions I had:
1) Can you remember when Mum and Dad moved to Grimsby
2) Did they go straight to Cabourne Road?
3) When did you go to a) Yorkshire b) Scotland

She said that she couldnt recall personally when they came back, but that when they did it was to stay at the Central Parade address (Where Grandad died). She believes that they couldnt have come before the end of the war, because of Dad's job working on munitions. So, the  earliest can only be 1946. She recalls that they were only a short while there before moving to Nunsthorpe; she remembers starting school (Macauley School) from there, so say 6 when started school, that would be 1948. This would allow 4 years at Cabourne before my birth which sounds about right. So, lets say they came over 1947.

She also confirmed that Dick got married in Grimsby in 1944 and Dot and he went to Gainsborough to live with Kathy(?) before moving to Habrough. (I believe that Dick never lived in Grimsby, but went straight to the Railway Hotel owned by Dot's father. She would help him run that while Dick worked on the docks, where he brought Dad over, before they both went off to Titans. Not surre how long they were at Gainsborough.

Laina left Grimsby for West Riding (Cleckheaton) in 1964; and moved to Aberdeen in 1972.  </text>
    </note>
    <note handle="_dc9c34c731c32882b4215205617" change="1516021615" id="N0001" type="Person Note">
      <text>1911 Census note looks like first name may be Beatrice</text>
    </note>
    <note handle="_dc9d065dcab3fcc6d39fe2982d" change="1516043592" id="N0002" type="Attribute Note">
      <text>Regiment = Sherwood Foresters (Nottinghamshire &amp; Derbyshire Regiment)
Unit / Battalion = 3rd Reserve Battalion</text>
    </note>
    <note handle="_e0b346bb374463e7581dc24e89a" change="1516043592" id="N0005" type="Attribute Note">
      <text>Regiment = Sherwood Foresters (Nottinghamshire &amp; Derbyshire Regiment)
Unit / Battalion = 3rd Reserve Battalion</text>
    </note>
    <note handle="_e0b346bb84f30efe962da283be8" change="1516021615" id="N0004" type="Person Note">
      <text>1911 Census note looks like first name may be Beatrice</text>
    </note>
    <note handle="_e0b346bbc746458a70fef27e4c0" change="1514913728" id="N0003" type="Source Note">
      <text>Telephone conversation on 2nd Jan 2018

Basically, Laina phoned back in response to 3 questions I had:
1) Can you remember when Mum and Dad moved to Grimsby
2) Did they go straight to Cabourne Road?
3) When did you go to a) Yorkshire b) Scotland

She said that she couldnt recall personally when they came back, but that when they did it was to stay at the Central Parade address (Where Grandad died). She believes that they couldnt have come before the end of the war, because of Dad's job working on munitions. So, the  earliest can only be 1946. She recalls that they were only a short while there before moving to Nunsthorpe; she remembers starting school (Macauley School) from there, so say 6 when started school, that would be 1948. This would allow 4 years at Cabourne before my birth which sounds about right. So, lets say they came over 1947.

She also confirmed that Dick got married in Grimsby in 1944 and Dot and he went to Gainsborough to live with Kathy(?) before moving to Habrough. (I believe that Dick never lived in Grimsby, but went straight to the Railway Hotel owned by Dot's father. She would help him run that while Dick worked on the docks, where he brought Dad over, before they both went off to Titans. Not surre how long they were at Gainsborough.

Laina left Grimsby for West Riding (Cleckheaton) in 1964; and moved to Aberdeen in 1972.</text>
    </note>
